      <hedline>
        <hl1>Built-In Telnet</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Furtkamp letter on Aug 31 Q &amp; A article on Telnet</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Q &amp; A on Telnet (''Telnet Still Available for Cruising the Web,'' Aug. 31) missed the fact that Windows 95, 98, NT and 2000 all have a built-in Telnet client. A more direct way to use Telnet on your Windows computer is go from the Start menu to the Run box, then type ''telnet'' and the address of the host computer.</p>
        <p>ROBERT FURTKAMP  Pocatello, Idaho</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
